## System Constants

| Constant | Value | Description |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| GOTCHI_WIDTH | 64.0f | Sprite width in pixels |
| GOTCHI_HEIGHT | 64.0f | Sprite height in pixels |
| GOTCHI_MOVE_SPEED | 50.0f | Movement speed (pixels/second) |
| GOTCHI_WANDER_SPEED | 20.0f | Wander movement speed |
| GOTCHI_TICK_RATE | 1.0f | Base tick interval (seconds) |
| WANDER_MIN_TIME | 2.0f | Minimum wander interval |
| WANDER_MAX_TIME | 3.5f | Maximum wander interval |

---

## Thread Safety Notes

- Gotchi operates on main game thread
- No mutex protection for stats (assumes single-threaded game loop)
- Serialization should occur between ticks to avoid partial updates

---

## Performance Considerations

1. **Tick Optimization**: Stats are only calculated once per tick, not per frame
2. **Mood Caching**: `moodCache` stores previously calculated mood properties
3. **Overlay Management**: Expired overlays are removed during processMoodOverlays()
4. **Animation Frames**: Loaded once at init, reused from texture arrays

---

